    <preface id="introduction" version="5.0" xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
        <title>Introduction</title>
        <para>This is the user guide for <application>@PROJECT_LONGNAME@</application> by @PROJECT_VENDOR@.
        If you have any questions that are not answered in this document please
        <ulink url="@ORG_CONTACT@">contact us</ulink> and let us know so that we can answer your
        questions and improve this guide.</para>

        <section id="open-source">
            <title>Open source</title>
            <para>Open-source is a very broad term, @PROJECT_LONGNAME@ in particular is released under the GPL v3 license, since @PROJECT_LONGNAME@ version 1.2.</para>
            <para>Being open source software has multiple (very good) implications. First of all, it means that @PROJECT_LONGNAME@ is now completely free! Yes, free! Everyone can freely download, use and distribute @PROJECT_LONGNAME@, forever. Secondly, the source code is now publicly available at <ulink ref="https://github.com/iPenguin/CrochetCharts">https://github.com/iPenguin/CrochetCharts</ulink>. Anyone can make changes, add new features, fix bugs,.. . As long as there are people willing to work on it, development won't halt!  Thirdly, you are allowed to share and redistribute @PROJECT_LONGNAME@ however you please, although it must always remain under this license.</para>
            <para>Being licensed under the GPL v3 license also means that the program comes without warranty. we will do our best to offer support for the program, but should it suddenly decide to sell your house and move to the cloud, we are not held responsible... ;-)</para>
        </section>

        <section id="what-is-new">
            <title>What's new in this version?</title>
            <para>Version 1.2 comes with a series of new features and fixes. Following is a hopefully exhaustive list.</para>

            <variablelist>
               <?dbfo list-presentation="blocks"?> 
               <varlistentry>
                   <term><link linkend="open-source">open source</link></term>
                   <listitem>
                       <para>@PROJECT_LONGNAME@ is now completely open source!</para>
                   </listitem>
               </varlistentry>

               <?dbfo list-presentation="blocks"?> 
               <varlistentry>
                   <term>Improved stability</term>
                   <listitem>
                       <para>The stability of the program has drastically improved. The program now rarely, if ever, crashes.</para>
                   </listitem>
               </varlistentry>

               <?dbfo list-presentation="blocks"?> 
               <varlistentry>
                   <term><link linkend="properties">Properties window</link></term>
                   <listitem>
                       <para>The <emphasis>properties window</emphasis> provides context sensitive information about the current selection and allows you to change certain properties of the selection.</para>
                   </listitem>
               </varlistentry>

               <?dbfo list-presentation="blocks"?> 
               <varlistentry>
                   <term><link linkend="export-charts">More export options</link></term>
                   <listitem>
                       <para>Extra export options, allowing you to export only the selection and the ability to add a header and/or footer to the exported chart.</para>
                   </listitem>
               </varlistentry>

               <?dbfo list-presentation="blocks"?> 
               <varlistentry>
                   <term><link linkend="pattern-colors">Full coloring options</link></term>
                   <listitem>
                       <para>The foreground and background of stitches can now be fully colored using the <link linkend="tools-color-edit">color edit tool</link> and the <link linkend="pattern-colors">pattern colors tab</link>.</para>
                   </listitem>
               </varlistentry>
                   
               <?dbfo list-presentation="blocks"?> 
               <varlistentry>
                   <term><link linkend="tools-indicator-edit">Full text support</link></term>
                   <listitem>
                       <para>Using the <link linkend="properties">properties window</link>, the font and size of an indicator can be edited, which allows for the user to write instructions, copyright notices,.. in the chart.</para>
                   </listitem>
               </varlistentry>

               <?dbfo list-presentation="blocks"?> 
               <varlistentry>
                   <term><link linkend="tools-add-image">Image support</link></term>
                   <listitem>
                       <para>It is possible to add custom images to the chart.</para>
                   </listitem>
               </varlistentry>

               <?dbfo list-presentation="blocks"?> 
               <varlistentry>
                   <term><link linkend="tools-selection-box">More selection methods</link></term>
                   <listitem>
                       <para>Box, lasso and line selection are available. These make it easier to select big groups of items quickly.</para>
                   </listitem>
               </varlistentry>

               <?dbfo list-presentation="blocks"?> 
               <varlistentry>
                   <term><link linkend="tools-mirror-rotate">Updated copy, mirror and rotate window</link></term>
                   <listitem>
                       <para>The old mirror and rotate window now has an extra option, <emphasis>copy</emphasis>, which clones and moves the whole selection. Mirror now properly mirrors the selection, rather than rotating it.</para>
                   </listitem>
               </varlistentry>

               <?dbfo list-presentation="blocks"?> 
               <varlistentry>
                   <term><link linkend="tools-grid-square">Align to grid</link></term>
                   <listitem>
                       <para>A square, rond and triangular grid can be shown, and all items will automatically snap to this grid. This is useful to exactly position elements in a chart. Snap to angle makes stitches automatically rotate towards the center in a round grid.</para>
                   </listitem>
               </varlistentry>

               <?dbfo list-presentation="blocks"?> 
               <varlistentry>
                   <term><link linkend="layers">Layers</link></term>
                   <listitem>
                       <para>A chart can be divided into multiple layers, making it easier to organize big charts and work with overlapping elements.</para>
                   </listitem>
               </varlistentry>

               <?dbfo list-presentation="blocks"?> 
               <varlistentry>
                   <term>New file format</term>
                   <listitem>
                       <para>@PROJECT_LONGNAME@ now internally uses another file format. Because of this, charts created in this version can't be opened in older version of @PROJECT_LONGNAME@</para>
                   </listitem>
               </varlistentry>

               <?dbfo list-presentation="blocks"?> 
               <varlistentry>
                   <term>New method of calculating rotation and scale</term>
                   <listitem>
                       <para>The application works with rotation and scale in a completely new way. Everything can now be rotated and scaled arbitrarily, without deforming the stitch or making it jump around the chart.</para>
                   </listitem>
               </varlistentry>

               <?dbfo list-presentation="blocks"?> 
               <varlistentry>
                   <term><link linkend="options-preferences">More options</link></term>
                   <listitem>
                       <para>More options have been added to the application, allowing for more custumizability. Among those options are the ability to rotate and scale around the center of a stitch, and the ability to center stitches on the mouse when pasting.</para>
                   </listitem>
               </varlistentry>

               <?dbfo list-presentation="blocks"?> 
               <varlistentry>
                   <term><link linkend="tools-resize">Resize window</link></term>
                   <listitem>
                       <para>A resize window allows you to change the size of the chart.</para>
                   </listitem>
               </varlistentry>
            </variablelist>


        </section>

